Why this happens

Rails is a meta-gem.

gem 'rails'


actually pulls in:

rails
 â”œâ”€ actionpack
 â”œâ”€ activerecord
 â”œâ”€ activesupport
 â”œâ”€ actionmailer
 â”œâ”€ actionview
 â”œâ”€ railties


So Bundler must update all of these together.

With --conservative
bundle update rails --conservative


ğŸ‘‰ This means:

Update Rails only as much as needed

Avoid updating other gems unless unavoidable

This is the recommended command for upgrades.

